# gdlint config (gdtoolkit 4.x). Only the file-lines ceiling is overridden;
# every other rule keeps its default (merged in by gdtoolkit). The integrator
# hub scripts/systems/world/world.gd is, by design, "the only place that knows
# about all subsystems at once" and grows by ~150 lines each feature phase. After
# eight phases it exceeds the arbitrary 1000-line default. Per-phase wiring that
# is self-contained is extracted into sibling rigs (e.g. ferromancy_rig.gd), but
# the irreducible build-order + signal-routing wiring lives in world.gd. This
# ceiling tunes one size heuristic; it does not disable any correctness lint.
max-file-lines: 1200
